Quick little smith machine squat tutorial 

One thing I really like about the smith machine is it kind of forces you into the correct squat position. I really like these for beginner’s because you can quickly understand what it feels like to be in the correct position and eliminates the instability of a barbell squat or DB squat.

Of course you want to do other squat variations that makes you gain that core strength and stability but this is really good for beginners and also for advanced lifters who want to really focus on using only those leg muscles to move the weight.

How to be a successful content creator 

Yea there’s hella other factors but here’s some key things if you just getting started.

Do what you do- there is literally an audience for EVERYTHING. I hate ASMR lmao but apparently everybody else loves it. Just do what you want to do.

Do it well- you have to be good at what you do if you want people to pay attention, people also love to see people’s journey too so don’t be scared to start now and get better over time.

Do it often- you have to be consistent I can’t stress that enough. You have to find a way to stay relevant and keep people ate and being consistent is a factor in that.

Don’t fix what ain’t broke- lmao I’m thirst trapper of the year 😂 but I’m not bouta fix what’s not broke I can continuously get 15-30k likes on the same exact video just done slightly different. If the people enjoy it and you enjoy doing it then keep doing it.

Have tough skin- don’t let the weirdos discourage you and scare you off social media. Let them be miserable behind they screen.

I used to let people below me belittle me, now I step on them proudly.

This fitness lifestyle is just like everything else in life, trial and error. What works for one person may not work for you. You have to find your lane and thrive in it. 

Practice don’t make perfect, whoever said that is a lie. Practice makes progress. Stop giving up when shit gets hard take a few steps back and try that shit again. Nobody’s going to judge you and if they do, fuck em 🤷🏾‍♂️

Things I’ve learned while being single 🙌🏾

1. Single doesn’t mean alone- just because we’re single doesn’t mean we are alone. We have to prioritize other relationships outside of romantic ones also. 

2. Not every good woman/man is the right one- just because someone isn’t a bad person and may posses some good qualities we look for doesn’t mean they are the right one for you. The right one will have all of the tangible qualities ( Looks, faithful, funny, etc) along with the intangibles. The intangibles are qualities in a person that make you a better you. They make you look at life different and want to just be better overall.

3. I had to stop “not asking for a lot”- safe to say we all have said plenty times “I don’t even ask for a lot” and that may very well be the issue. We all need to have non-negotiables. These are the things that a person must have or ✌🏾.

4. Peace > Temporary satisfaction - We all do this, we choose temporary satisfaction over our overall peace of mind and mental and emotional health. It’s convenient and it’s easy and that’s why it’s hard to break, let’s do better. 

5. I don’t need to look for my person they will come - Stop stepping out of your lane looking for your person. Your person will be on the same path as you and and you will cross paths while you are being who you are and doing what you do.

I love Fitness and Food 🏋🏾‍♂️🍴

There’s a lot of diets out there even people who will tell you that you need to cut this and cut that out of your diet when realistically everything is okay in moderation.

If you want longevity with the fitness lifestyle you have to understand that it’s about sustainability. If you’re on this strict diet you can’t realistically sustain then you’re eventually going to fall into some bad habits such as binge eating. 

Save yourself the stopping and starting because you keep “falling off” from your diet and gain a healthy relationship with food.

Life’s about balance 

As a trainer I push people past their limits and put their bodies through a lot of stress. Recovering from that stress is essential.

Now I’m learning to ease that stress and help your body recover. Massage therapy is next of many things added to my belt.

“The weight of the world on your shoulders”

We hold so much tension in our necks and shoulders. When we are stressed our shoulders raise causing tension. Think about it your shoulders are probably raised right now. 

Be conscious about relaxing your shoulders and releasing that tension, set an alarm in your phone and label it “relax your shoulders” you’ll be surprised how often your shoulders are raised.

Regular massages will also help ease that tension. 💆🏾‍♀️

Stop beating yourself up.

This is a reminder that the number on the scale is bullshit 90% of the time. All of my youth I wanted to “be big” I wanted to be 180lbs then 200lbs and 215lbs but I quickly realized that number on the scale rarely reflected how I actually wanted to look and I was beating myself up year after year for no reason.

Prioritize how you look in the mirror, feel on the inside, how your clothes fit, how much stronger and healthier you are.

Easier said than done I know but I promise it’s what you need to understand.

Last thing, BE PATIENT. This is not supposed to be a quick and easy process. It takes a long time to build muscle and hit these goals, enjoy the small wins along the way.

4. Search for agencies in your area. Be very selective with this. 

5. Practice being comfortable in front of a camera. This part of critical. The more comfortable and natural you are the more clients will want to book you .

My top 3 things beginners should know based on my experience this far.

1. Get into a acting class! There’s so many different options for this. You can do virtual or in person so there’s no excuse. This will help you understand what kind of acting you want to do. It will help you lay the groundwork to understanding what it takes to become an actor. It will help you understand the art of acting without ACTING… you’ll understand that part later.

2. Download actors access and backstage. More than likely you won’t have an agent to start off so there is where you can find acting opportunities.

3. Throw that fear away. I promise you if you are afraid to look stupid, sound stupid, be made fun of, etc acting ain’t for you until you can get passed that. You HAVE to become vulnerable and open to showing deep parts of yourself, looking goofy & being uncomfortable.
